Program: The Why Factor
Title: Memorialisation
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p029p7l3
Last Broadcast Date: New Year's Day 2015
How do we remember the dead and why does it matter? Mike Williams considers the promise of so many nations never to forget the death and suffering of World War One, and explores how the dead have been remembered around the world and through the ages. Produced by Ben Crighton Image: Ceramic poppies covered in rainwater at the Blood Swept Lands and Seas of Red evolving art installation at the Tower of London Credit: Chris Jackson/PA Wire Show less